<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-655-293  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 655 293.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Dec 3 1990 v7 n48 p153(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New plan outlined to restore health at Businessland.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fisher, Susan E.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Businessland Inc executives at the annual stockholder meeting inlate Nov 1990 renew their pledge to promote customizedapplications.andP;  The executives also vow to cut expenses.andP;  Observersare unsure about Businessland's prospects for success in providingcustomized applications to corporate customers.andP;  The retail chainalso announces that it will work with Dallas-based systemsintegrator Perot Systems Corp to design and install an automatedmicrocomputer purchasing system, called CleanStream, for EastmanKodak Co. The customized application service will be part ofBusinessland's new Network Systems group; other newly establishedgroups are General Products, Distribution and Service.andO;Businessland is already struggling to make money in suchvalue-added services as technical support and consulting.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Businessland Inc. (Management).andO;Ticker:    BLI.andO;Topic:     ReorganizationLossesFinancial StabilityAnnualComputer ServicesComputer Retailing.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The new shape of Businessland. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Susan E. FisherandM;SAN JOSE, Calif.andP;  -- Troubled Businessland Inc. once again is attempting toturn its losses around, promoting itself as a provider of customizedapplications in addition to low-cost PCs.andM;At the company's annual meeting here last week, executives promised to cutexpenses while delivering higher levels of service.andP;  Although the reseller isstill struggling to make money from such value-added services as consultingand technical support, company officials said Businessland now will offercustomized PC applications.andM;Edward Simon, Businessland's new president, said the customized applicationsbusiness is essential to Businessland's attempt to restore profitability.andM;&quot;It is truly the missing link in what [CEO] Dave Norman would call 'thecomputer company,' &quot; Simon said.andM;Initially, Businessland hopes to customize applications for corporatecustomers in such areas as insurance and finance, said Leslie McNeill, whojoined the company two months ago as its vice president of strategicplanning.andP;  Businessland will team up with software developers whose productsare not widely distributed to design specialized applications, he said.andM;To launch Businessland's new effort, the company announced the signing of acontract with Eastman Kodak Co. to design and install an automated PCpurchasing system called CleanStream.andP;  Businessland is developing thePC-based system with its partner, Perot Systems Corp., a Dallas-based systemsintegrator.andM;The customized application service will be part of Businessland's new NetworkSystems unit, one of four recently established divisions individuallyresponsible for their own profits and losses (see chart, Page 153).andP;  Thedivision is expected to contribute one-third of Businessland's revenue withinfive years, McNeill said.andM;Although the emphasis on customized applications is new, analysts said thetwo-pronged strategy is one the reseller has failed to execute effectively inthe past.andP;  While Businessland officials have promised to give corporatecustomers both competitive prices and specialized service, the company hasplunged deeper into the red.andM;Pointing to financial losses in the $20 million range for the last quarter,critics said that to get customers to pay for service, Businessland has toprove it truly can add value to products.andM;Joe Sasso, assistant vice president of the Management Services Division ofBarclay's Bank in New York, said Businessland's reorganization has come toolate and that the reseller has lost credibility with the bank.andP;  SinceBusinessland failed to fulfill an order on time, Barclay's no longer buyshardware from the company.andO;</TEXT></DOC>